{
  "texts": [
    "The weighted RAG model reduced such errors to 9.7%, compared to 14.2% for the baseline model.",
    "Another common error was the over-reliance on certain high-weight documents, leading to biased outputs that did not fully consider the broader context.",
    "The weighted RAG model exhibited an 8.5% occurrence of this error, as opposed to 11.8% for the baseline.",
    "Additionally, the model occasionally struggled with highly specialized knowledge, producing outputs that were superficially accurate but lacked depth.",
    "The incidence of errors in specialized knowledge was 12.1% for the weighted RAG model, compared to 15.5% for the baseline."
  ]
}